Nov 10 2009 	Perfect weekend getaway	My husband and I just returned from a long weekend in San Francisco. We stayed at the Kensington Park Hotel and this is where we will stay if/when we return to the city. The location is perfect - it's literally in the heart of Union Square. Union Square, to me, was definitely touristy and not really my favorite part of town, but the central location is perfect. My husband and I love to walk around and explore the city and this allowed for us to do so very easily. Also, if you're new to San Fran, you feel really safe because there are always lots of people around. Additionally, there are great amenities (Walgreens, coffee shops, breakfast places, etc) right around the corner. When we arrived at the Kensington Park Hotel, we were very impressed immediately with how cute the lobby is and also how friendly the staff is. We were early in our arrival and they gave us several choices of rooms (explained front vs. back of building; choice of king v. queen bed, etc). Our room didn't disappoint. It faced a building, but we didn't care - the room is a great size (definitely a city hotel size) and the bathroom was pretty large as well. Our bathroom only had a shower (once again, they had given us a choice upon check in) but it suited us just fine and it was actually really large. The Kensington staff is tremendous. Everyone was incredibly friendly and helpful and definitely wanted to make sure we had a great stay. This hotel is the perfect &quot;boutique-y&quot; hotel and we will definitely stay there again.	
