Sep 23 2009 	Loved it!	We booked our vacation package to SF from Montreal via Yahoo travel. We decided on the Kensington Park Hotel based on reviews on TripAdvisor and price comparisons. The Kensington Park Hotel is value for money considering its rooms are comfortable and clean, and the fact that it's in the middle of all the action. Actually, we were surprised that the rate was so affordable. The staff were friendly and helpful, the bed was very comfortable, and the room was clean (I paid special notice to the bathroom because I'm finicky about these things). It's true there is no air conditioning (there is a ceiling fan), but we didn't need it anyway during our stay as the weather was cool. I had read some reviews complaining about street noise, but we experienced no problems in this department. Before traveling, I requested a king size bed and/or a room on an upper floor if possible, and they were able to accommodate us with both things. We were not disturbed by outside noise on the 9th floor. All in all, for an expensive city that was full of tourists at the time, we felt we got a great deal at this hotel, and I'll likely stay there again the next time I visit San Francisco.	
